Raw transmutation to `u32`.

This is currently identical to `transmute::<f32, u32>(self)` on all platforms.

See [`from_bits`](about:blank/primitive.f32.html#method.from_bits "associated function f32::from_bits") for some discussion of the portability of this operation (there are almost no issues).

Note that this function is distinct from `as` casting, which attempts to preserve the _numeric_ value, and not the bitwise value.

